<section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pb-32">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-zinc-100 mb-6">
            Why enforcement, not detection
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-zinc-400 mb-4">
            Detection tools raise alerts you have to triage. Hangar's policies are
            deterministic: a tool call is allowed or it is not &mdash; admission policy on
            the server spec, per-server egress rules, tool-schema pinning, and approval
            gates on the call path.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-zinc-400">
            Binary outcomes: no anomaly scores to tune, no baseline to train. If your
            platform team can review a NetworkPolicy, they can review a Hangar policy.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
